paper.comment: DESY-HERA. Measurement of the Dijet cross sections in neutral current deep inelastic scattering of 27.5 GeV postirons on 820 GeV protons. The cross sections are measured in the Breit Frame using the kT jet alogrithm. The data were collected during the 1996 and 1997 HERA runnning periods and have an integrated luminsoity of 38.4 +- 0.6 pb.-1. The following conditions hold for all the tables:. E(P=1) = 27.5 GeV. E(P=2) = 820 GeV. Y > 0.04. ET(P=4,RF=BREIT) > 8 GeV. ET(P=5,RF=BREIT) > 5 GeV. ET(P=4,RF=LAB) > 5 GeV. ET(P=5,RF=LAB) > 5 GeV. ABS(ETARAP(P=3,4,RF=LAB)) < 2. E(P=3) > 10 GeV. The variable XI is defined as X*(1+M(P_4_5)**2/Q**2 and MEAN(ET) is the average transverse energy of the two jets with highest transverse energy in the event.. In the tables the column headed ISR/FSR is the multiplicative correction which has been applied to account for effects if initial and final-state QED radiation. The second DSYS (systematic) error in the tables is the uncertainty in the jet-energy-scale.
